  "Ethics in Data Collection": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "What is a 'conflict of interest' in research?": "",
  "Conflicts of interest arise when researchers have financial ties, personal relationships, or other interests that could consciously or unconsciously bias their research.": "",
  "The Tuskegee Syphilis Study is an example of:": "",
  "The Tuskegee study withheld effective treatment from African American men with syphilis for decades without informed consent, leading to the Belmont Report and modern ethical standards.": "",
  "A medical study in a developing country tests a new malaria treatment by giving the experimental drug to local villagers and comparing their outcomes to untreated villagers. The same study design would never be approved in the researchers' home country because a standard treatment exists. What ethical principle from the Belmont Report is being violated?": "",
  "The principle of justice requires that research burdens and benefits be distributed fairly. Conducting a study in a developing country that would be considered unethical at home exploits a vulnerable population.": ""
}